This project reads and republishes text derived from the CBETA XML-P5 corpus:

  Chinese Buddhist Electronic Text Association (CBETA)
  https://github.com/cbeta-org/xml-p5
  https://www.cbeta.org

Per CBETA's terms, the corpus is "available for non-commercial use when
distributed with [the TEI] header intact." This site is non-commercial,
carries no advertising, and does not sell access to the texts. The
extracted plain-text paragraphs served by this site retain their CBETA
identifier (canon/volume/number) and link back to the original file in
cbeta-org/xml-p5 so provenance is always traceable.

Some texts in the corpus are drawn from other collections credited within
CBETA itself, including 太虛大師全書, 印順法師著作集, 演培法師全集, and
呂澂佛學著作集 — see each text's header for its specific source and
rights holder.
